<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="319" type="composition">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="319">Composition.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="319">
Six Neotropical species: 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Sidymella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sidymella excavata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="excavata">Sidymella excavata</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. furcillata" pageId="0" pageNumber="319" rank="species" species="furcillata">S. furcillata</taxonomicName>
(Keyserling, 1880), 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. longispina" pageId="0" pageNumber="319" rank="species" species="longispina">S. longispina</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mello-Leitão">Mello-Leitao</normalizedToken>
, 1943), 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. lucida" pageId="0" pageNumber="319" rank="species" species="lucida">S. lucida</taxonomicName>
(Keyserling, 1880), 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. marmorata" pageId="0" pageNumber="319" rank="species" species="marmorata">S. marmorata</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., and 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. kolpogaster" pageId="0" pageNumber="319" rank="species" species="kolpogaster">S. kolpogaster</taxonomicName>
(Lise, 1973); 11 additional species from the Australasian region that are not within the scope of the present study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="319" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="319">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="319">Ecuador, Colombia, Peru, Brazil, Argentina, and Uruguay (Fig. 15).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
